++- `src/proctor/triggers/__init__.py` — exports `SchedulerTrigger`
++
++**Implementation details:**
++- `__init__` stores schedules list and empty tasks list
++- `start(bus)` creates one `asyncio.create_task` per enabled schedule item (cron or interval)
++- `stop()` cancels all tasks with `contextlib.suppress(CancelledError)`, matching `TerminalTrigger` pattern
++- `_run_cron(item, bus)` uses `croniter` to compute next fire time, sleeps until then, publishes event; skips past times
++- `_run_interval(item, bus)` sleeps for `interval_seconds`, then publishes
++- Events published as `Event(type="trigger.scheduler", source=f"scheduler:{item.name}", payload=item.payload)`
